# Fix Hyprland Configuration Errors

The system is displaying Hyprland configuration errors on startup due to deprecated options and incorrect syntax usage (mixing `windowrulev2` syntax with `windowrule`).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The changes involve modifying core Hyprland configuration files for the Omarchy distribution. We are switching from `windowrule` to `windowrulev2` which is the recommended modern syntax and fix the deprecated option errors.

## Proposed Changes

### Omarchy Default Config

#### [MODIFY] [looknfeel.conf](file:///home/rob/.local/share/omarchy/default/hypr/looknfeel.conf)
- Comment out the deprecated `misc:new_window_takes_over_fullscreen` option.

#### [MODIFY] [windows.conf](file:///home/rob/.local/share/omarchy/default/hypr/windows.conf)
- Convert `windowrule` directives to `windowrulev2`.
- `suppressevent maximize` is only supported in `windowrulev2`.
- `class:` and `title:` selectors are `windowrulev2` syntax.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- Run `hyprctl reload` to apply changes.
- Check `~/.cache/hyprland/hyprland.log` (typical log location) or `journalctl` for any remaining config errors.
- Ideally, the "red box" error overlay should disappear from the user's screen immediately after reload (which the user can confirm, or we can infer from absence of new logs).
